Source: ggz-server
Section: games
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Josef Spillner <dr_maux@users.sourceforge.net>
Standards-Version: 3.5.2
Build-Depends: debhelper (>> 3.0.0), autoconf, automake, libtool

Package: ggzd
Architecture: any
Section: games
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}
Description: GGZ Gaming Zone Main Server
 This server is not required if you want to play online games,
 but it will be needed if you intend to do game hosting on your
 own, be it for having an own little server or for development
 purposes.
 .
 It loads all required game servers dynamically, so you can
 start very quickly. It is, however, very configurable.

Package: ggz-game-servers
Architecture: any
Section: games
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}
Description: GGZ Gaming Zone Game Servers
 All internal GGZ games currently available are included in this
 package.
 The following games are waiting to be played:
 chess, chinese-checkers, combat, dots, ggzcards, hastings
 krosswater, lapocha, muehle, reversi, spades, tictactoe

Package: libggzdmod0
Architecture: any
Section: libs
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}
Description: Game server library for GGZ games
 This library provides all necessary function for GGZ-compliant
 game servers.

Package: libggzdmod-dev
Architecture: any
Section: devel
Depends: libggzdmod0 (= ${Source-Version}), libc6-dev, libggz-dev (>= 0.0.5-1), libexpat1-dev (>= 1.95.2-6)
Description: Game server library for GGZ game - development files
 In order to develop your own GGZ game servers, you need to
 install this package.

